            <title>[LU-16258] Explicitly support .splice_write</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16258</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160; Linux commit v5.9-rc1-6-g36e2c7421f02&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; &#160; fs: don&apos;t allow splice read/write without explicit ops&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; Lustre supports splice_write and previously provide handlers&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; for splice_read.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; Explicitly use iter_file_splice_write, if it exists.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
